{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 01:16:00.113698", "event": "llm_end", "text": "I have submitted the solution.\n\nSummary:\n- Anomaly: Yes\n- Faulty device: external_router_1\n- Root cause: Misconfiguration causing route leakage of 20.0.0.0/24 into the internal domain (selected: bgp_blackhole_route_leak)\n\nNote: The diagnosis describes RIP route leakage, but the available root cause types did not include a RIP-specific option. The closest available category was used to represent unintended route advertisement/leak.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1822, "output_tokens": 99, "total_tokens": 1921, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
